Key Match Events: Mitchell Santner took five for 59 with his left-arm spin as the Netherlands were bowled out for 223 in 46.3 overs.
Devon Conway and Will Young provided a solid stand of 67, but Conway holed out at long-on after scoring 32.
Rachin Ravindra and Will Young compiled a 77-run stand before New Zealand tried to switch gears in the latter half of the innings.
Daryl Mitchell, who was dropped on 22, and Tom Latham then put on 53 before the Dutch hit back in the last powerplay with three quick wickets for 16 runs.
Santner provided the Black Caps with a perfect finish by slamming Bas de Leede (one for 64) for two consecutive sixes in the last over, which went for 23.
Post-Match Reflections: Mitchell Santner became the first New Zealand spinner to take a five-wicket haul at a Cricket World Cup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: New Zealand had already avenged their narrow defeat in the 2019 World Cup final after beating England by nine wickets in Ahmedabad last week.
